1. *Šalite* se, zar nije ovo najbolji vic ikada? (You're joking, isn't this the best joke ever?)
2. Ne *šalim* se kada kažem da je ovo najbolji restoran u gradu. (I'm not joking when I say this is the best restaurant in town.)
3. Oni se uvijek *šale* na moj račun, ali to mi ne smeta. (They always joke about me, but it doesn't bother me.)
4. *Šalio* sam se kada sam rekao da ću kupiti novi automobil. (I was joking when I said I would buy a new car.)
5. Da li se ti *šališ* ili stvarno misliš to što govoriš? (Are you joking or do you really mean what you're saying?)
6. Oni su *se šalili* dok nisu shvatili da su povrijedili nekoga. (They were joking until they realized they had hurt someone.)
7. Da li bi mogao da prestaneš *da se šališ* i ozbiljno razgovaramo? (Could you stop joking and let's have a serious conversation?)
8. *Šalite* se ako mislite da mogu da popijem ovu cijelu bocu vina. (You're joking if you think I can drink this whole bottle of wine.)
9. Kada se neko uvrijedi, trebali bi prestati *sa šalama*. (When someone gets offended, we should stop with the jokes.)
10. Ja ne mogu da vjerujem da si *se šalio* na njen račun. (I can't believe you were joking about her.)